description:
Responsibilities
To design, develop and conduct training programmes to ensure trainees obtain adequate skills and knowledge to provide quality services to the customers including but not restricted to classroom, on-site, systems-related or e-learning operational training;
To evaluate and review the training programmes to ensure training requirements and effectiveness are met;
To train the trainers appointed by both internal and external parties including operations contractors, Cargo Agents, and Government parties;
To maintain and update all training materials in line with the latest operating procedures and instructions;
To conduct assessment on the proficiency of trainees under probation as and when required;
To ensure training records of all trainees are complete and up-to-date;
To support Quality Control and conduct inspections for improving the operations quality;
To complete special projects and other requirements assigned by supervisor.

 Requirement

F.7 or tertiary education preferably in Logistics, Aviation Management, Training and Development or related discipline.
Minimum 3 years of solid working experience in aviation industry, air cargo terminal, logistics company, warehouse or freight forwarding Company, of which minimum 2 years in providing staff training or performing supervisory duties;
Hands-on experience in the air-cargo terminal operations would be beneficial;
DG license (Cat. 6) holder is preferable;
Knowledge and experience in e-learning is an advantage;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Strong planning, organising and analytical skills;
Good interpersonal & communication skills with proactive, tactful & result-oriented personality;
Able to work independently and under pressure;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Training Specialist 
To apply, you may email your confidential resume with date of availability, current and expected salary to recruitment @cpsl.com.hk. Applicants not contacted within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.
Cathay Pacific Services Limited is an Equal Opportunities Employer. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within six weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months.

This role is to ensure smooth line operations by conducting comprehensive flight routing planning and maintaining flight dispatch activities compliance of related laws and regulation. Also, this role works closely with pilots by updating latest flying conditions, and assist them to perform flights.

Responsibilities

Ensure all the HKA dispatch activities comply with the laws and regulations of Hong Kong as well as the relevant state and country laws;
Ensure information in the flight planning system database is up to date,  accurate and available to dispatch service;
Provide all-rounded administration support in the Line Operations section;
Review and evaluate the operational documents and relevant data, to ensure safety and security of company’s flight operations in accordance with standards and regulations;
Prepare EDTO flight packages; 
Conduct briefing and assist Pilot-in-Command (PIC) in flight preparation; and
Perform other ad-hoc duties as required.

Requirements:

5 years of operational control / flight dispatch experience;
Familiar with flight planning programme
Holder of FAA Aircraft Dispatcher License will be an advantage; and
Previous experience with ICAO and/or HKCAD regulations is preferable
Fluency in written and spoken English and Chinese

Candidate with less experience will be considered as Officer, Flight Dispatch

MAIN DUTIES/RESPONSIBILITIES:

a. Ensuring compliance with all relevant safety, security, quality, health and environmental procedures to ensure a healthy and safe work environment

b. Ensuring proper documentation is received and reviewed for ISBAO and CAA audits

c. Handling and supervising tasks in relation to delivery of new managed aircraft, including aircraft completion management, coordination with OEM, obtaining operational approval requests and follow-up with local CAA.

d. Liaising with manufacturers’ representatives to resolve problems and maintain good relationship with different CAA.

e. Manage and Monitor to the Documentations used in Support of Aircraft Operations and Maintenance such as Pilot License Validation, Aircraft Operating Approval and Letter of Authorization.

f. Manage and Monitor the Aircraft Certification such as Certificate of Airworthiness, Certificate of Registrations and Noise Certificate.

g. Managing an Aircraft Technical Library, maintain Aircraft related Manual subscription, updates and distribution.

h. Managing Flight Log entries into FOS and Post Flight Documents.

i. Monitor CFOQA report, arrange meeting

SKILLS & EXPERIENCE

Qualifications: 

a. Degree or above preferable; and

b. ICAO, IS-BAO or IATA Safety or Auditor Qualification.

Experience:

a. Operational experience, normally achieved as a flight deck crew member, engineer or equivalent experience in aviation management;

b. Experience in a Quality assurance role;

c. Exposure in the following:

           i. Flight safety philosophy;

           ii. Human factors and the decision-making process;

           iii. Accident prevention;

           iv. The role of the safety officer as advisor to senior management;

           v. Risk management;

           vi. Accident/incident management;

           vii. Safety management systems;

           viii. Emergency response planning; and

           ix. Incident investigation.

Skills:

a. Self-motivated with great initiative, well organized, detail-minded and flexible;

b. Must have a good command of English and Mandarin, written and spoken;

c. Good team player with excellent communication skills, competent in crisis management, planning and problem solving; and

d. Able to maintain the highest standard of safety and quality.

DEAR FUTURE TALENT, YOUR MOVE!

Being the new rising airline since 2013, we are the Hong Kong’s only Low Cost Carrier (LCC) offering you safe and flexible service options to Hong Kong and beyond.

We’re on a mission to inspire you to be different, to shake things up, to inspire the spirit of adventure by bringing you to fascinating destinations that few others serve.

Spread your wings and fly with us!


What will you do?  


Generate task duelist and identity potential overdue tasks and maintenance status from the system in daily basis, and report to Planner for abnormal status.
Verify movement log data by comparing flight log system and engineering control system;
Maintain aircraft component change in the system for scheduled maintenance including major components (including Engine, APU and LDG);
Monitor, maintain, and update loose equipment list/record in a regular basis;
Ensure light maintenance tasks are properly scheduled within its limitation;
Ensure in-house requirements (aircraft wash, CDC and pest control) are properly scheduled as per Technical Service requirements.
Prepare light maintenance work package/work order and submit to MRO in a sufficient period prior to the planned date, and follow up the work task enquiries, spare/tooling required, etc.;
Collect, feedback and update the accomplished record in the system;
Check and verify maintenance documents and consult with Technical Service or Fleet Technical Management when necessary;
Prepare and maintain monthly and weekly maintenance schedule, ensure the schedule can be properly implemented;
Arrange light maintenance task in a cost-effective way;
Verify monthly utilization report and provide to Manager, Engineering;
Assist Planning Engineer to prepare the necessary documents for C of A renewal (CMR) to Quality Assurance;
Support Ad-hoc duties as assigned.

We are a perfect match, if you are:


Minimum 2-year of experience (or above) in aircraft engineering and maintenance;
Minimum 2-year of experience in Production Planning & Control (PPC) or Maintenance Control Center (MCC);
Diploma Holder of Aircraft Engineering is preferred, Degree holder is a plus;
Aircraft Maintenance & Engineering License is preferred.

Your Future Work Life?

Work flexibly with staggered working hours and flexible workplace
Dress Casual and Smart everyday
Work in a newly-designed office with open seating, stylish breakout areas, game room, gym and free coffee…
Work with a group of energetic and multicultural professionals (up to 50 nationalities!)
Have great fun in Snack Friday, New Year Market, Fly with your Kids Day, Basketball Team…
Have your voice heard through Townhalls, Crew forums, CEO live sessions etc.

What will you enjoy?

Fly anywhere we fly for free plus taxes during leisure with your friends and family
Special privileges to buy duty free products
Career Express


You will be inspired by our core values.
You will be inspired by our vibrant, efficient and entrepreneurial spirit. Join our fun, collaborative and reliable team to ignite your dream!


Interested? It’s time to have YOUR MOVE!
If you're ready to embark your adventure, start by clicking the ‘Apply now’ and get on the plane to fly with HK Express!

Responsibilities: 

Perform ground handling services, including check-in, boarding gate, arrival, lost & found and ticketing services duties;
Meet and assist VIPs on departure and arrival;
Assist superior in flight disruption / creeping delay;
Carry out any other duties as required and directed by the Company.

Requirements:

Form 5 graduate or above with at least 5 subjects passed in HKCEE or minimum Level 2 in 5 HKDSE New Senior Secondary Subjects (including English and Chinese language) or equivalent;
Fresh graduate will also be considered;
Good command of spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Good customer services skills;
Willing to take shift duties;
Ability to work on own initiative
Immediate available is preferred

FLIGHT OPERATIONS OFFICER



You are expected to perform dispatch services and oversee duties related to pre-flight preparation, flight planning, crew briefing, and irregular operations handling in the Operations Control Centre.

Key Responsibilities:

Monitor, manage and provide up-to-date aeronautical information or documentation for Flight Crew and offices;
Assist FODM to control the daily operations to ensure safe, effective, and economical operations of Company aircraft;
Provide, monitor, communicate and distribute pertinent operational messages between aircraft and service partners, as necessary;
Initiate appropriate action regarding aircraft rotation aspects so as to achieve on-time-performance (OTP) and meet maintenance requirements;
Initiate appropriate action and notify the essential personnel in the event of flight disruption;
Liaise with the Engineering Department for aircraft serviceability issues;
Ensure smooth transfer of duty such that the relieving Flight Operations personnel is/are informed of all necessary matters including operational conditions in general during the duty period, NOTAM and weather information, operational instructions & documents, crew duty hours, and matters to be settled by the relieving Flight Operations personal.
Perform crew roster re-assignment to ensure no infringement on the Flight Time Limitation Scheme;
Other duties assigned by Department Manager.
Requirement:

Tertiary education in any discipline;
1-2 years’ aviation experience in flight operations, or have acted as a Flight Crew, Navigator, Air Traffic Controller, Crew Controller, or Flight Operations Officer;
Fluently read, write and understand English and Chinese;
Able to work on shift duty including overnight shift.
We offer a competitive compensation package to the successful candidate. Interested parties, please click “Apply Now” to submit your application no later than 7 February 2022.
Greater Bay Airlines is an Equal Opportunities employer. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Our Personal Information Collection Statement will be available upon your online application. Applicants not being notified within 8 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. Their personal data will be retained for a period of 12 months from the application date and will be destroyed thereafter.

Responsibilities:-

• Maintain shipment logs, prepare and handle shipping paperwork and documentation;
• Rate, route and facilitate the movement of shipments with the service standards as requested by the customers;
• File the airway bill and manifest;
• Input data for each air freight movement into the computer system;
• Coordinate with warehouse co-workers to facilitate the movement of the freight including pallet arrangement and relevant paperwork;
• Send pre-alert and relevant messages to appropriate parties;
• Trace airway bill copies from sub-loaders;
• Prepare invoice of consolidated shipment to various co-loading accounts.


Required Qualifications:-
- F.5 or above, preferably with educational background in shipping/logistics studies;
- Good communication skills, willing to learn and work under pressure; 
- Fair English and Mandarin;
- Need to work on shift (Day / Overnight shift duty);

We offer a rewarding package and company benefits including double pay, discretionary bonus, 15 days annual leave, medical insurance etc. If you are interested in the career opportunity stated above, please send your resume stating full details of your background, current and expected salaries to us.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Our data processing are compliant with data protection regulations. To learn about GEODIS Privacy Policy or exercise your rights, go to http://geodis.com/dp/recruitment-privacy-policy
